Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Remove the @British Beef Roasting Joint{400%g} from your fridge to bring it to room temperature. Pour enough oil into a deep #baking tray{} to cover the bottom and pop into the oven. Bring a large #saucepan{} of water with @salt{1/2%tsp} to the boil.

Peel and chop the @potatoes{450%g} into 4cm chunks, then boil for ~{7-8%minutes} or until the edges are soft. When ready, drain in a #colander{} and sprinkle on the @plain flour{1%tbsp} and @mixed herbs{1%tbsp}.

Shake to fluff them up, then carefully add them to the hot baking tray, turning in the oil. Season with @salt{}, then roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{45-50%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

In the meantime, peel and grate the @garlic cloves{3} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Transfer the beef to a baking tray. Drizzle with @olive oil{} and season generously with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}. Sprinkle over the @dried rosemary{2%sprigs} and half the garlic, rubbing it over the meat.

Roast on the middle shelf of your oven for ~{25-30%minutes} for medium-rare. Add an extra ~{5%minutes} if you like your beef more well done.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat. It's safe to eat when browned on the outside.

While everything roasts, trim the @carrots{3}, then halve lengthways (no need to peel). Chop into roughly 1cm wide, 5cm long batons.

When the beef has ~{20%minutes} left, pop the carrots onto the same baking tray. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}, then spread out in a single layer.

Roast for the remaining time until tender, ~{20-25%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Pour the @water for the Jus{300%ml} into the (now empty) #potato saucepan{} and bring to the boil on high heat.

Stir in the @red wine jus paste{30%g}, then reduce the heat to medium. Allow the sauce to bubble and thicken, stirring regularly, ~{10-12%minutes}.

When the carrots have ~{5%minutes} left, drizzle them with the @honey{1%tbsp} and return to the oven. Once the beef is cooked, rest it, wrapped loosely in #foil{}, for at least ~{10%minutes} before slicing.

== Mustard Creamed Spinach ==

While the beef rests, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Add the remaining garlic and fry for ~{1%minute}.

Stir through the @creme fraiche{75%g}, @wholegrain mustard{17%g} and @water for the Sauce{50%ml}. Cook until warmed through, ~{1-2%minutes}. Season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}.

Add the @baby spinach{100%g} to the pan a handful at a time until wilted and piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}. Remove from the heat.

== Assembly ==

When everything's ready, reheat the red wine jus. Slice your beef and share between your plates.

Serve with your honey glazed carrots, creamed mustard spinach and roast potatoes alongside.

Finish by spooning over the red wine jus. Enjoy!